episodes.title: Will the Epstein files bring down the British PM?
episodes.description: Donald Trump was Jeffrey Epstein’s one time friend and his name appears countless times in the Epstein files. But it’s not the US president who’s currently fighting for his political survival. Instead, it’s the British leader Keir Starmer who’s on very shaky ground, even though he’s not in the documents. Today, professor of politics at Deakin University, Simon Tormey, on how he became so deeply embroiled in the controversy. Featured: Simon Tormey, Executive Dean of Arts and Education and Professor of Politics at Deakin University Learn more about your ad choices. Visit megaphone.fm/adchoices
